<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<p>• Discover the highlights of Sardinia and go off the beaten track on this 8 day tour<br />• Staying in four-star hotels<br />• Knowledgeable tour manager throughout<br />• See the glamorous port town of Porto Cervo<br />• Full day trip to Corsica<br />• Visit the idyllic island of Maddalena and enjoy some free time relaxing on the white sandy beaches<br />• Head inland to the village of Aggius and learn about its ancient crafts<strong><br /></strong>• Wander through the walled city of Alghero<br />• Visit the picturesque seaside town of Bosa where colourful houses spill down the cliffs into the crystal-clear waters</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/secrets-of-sardinia#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Olbia</strong></p>
<p><span>Fly to Olbia airport where you’ll be greeted by your tour manager and transferred to your hotel in Porto Cervo. Enjoy an evening meal in the hotel restaurant.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Porto Cervo</strong></p>
<p><span>After a hearty breakfast, head into the glamorous seaside town of Porto Cervo built in the 60’s by the Aga Kahn. Whilst being a luxury resort, it retains a laid back Italian vibe. Admire the interesting architecture with Greek, Spanish, North African and Italian influences and browse the high-end shops. In the afternoon, head to the Santa Teresa di Gallura region at the northern tip of Sardinia. Here you’ll uncover the historical heritage of Sardinia with a visit to Complesso Nuragico di Lu Brandali with its nuraghe, ancient megalithic edifice. The complex dates back to the 14</span><sup>th</sup><span> and 10</span><sup>th</sup><span> centuries BC and is the site of the Giant’s Tomb, a gallery grave built by the Nuragic civilization in the Bronze Age. After, take a stroll along the scenic coastline to Capo Testa and admire the smooth granite rock formations, before heading back to the hotel in Porto Cervo for your evening meal.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Corsica</strong></p>
<p><span>Today the group heads back towards Santa Teresa di Gallura where you’ll catch the ferry across to the French island of Corsica (approx. 50 minutes). Whilst on board enjoy the stunning views across the glistening blue water as you head towards the port of Bonifacio. The medieval fortified citadel sits in pride of place atop the white limestone cliffs. Weave through the narrow streets, uncover the history, and soak up the atmosphere of this vibrant town, before making your journey back to your hotel in Porto Cervo.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Isola Maddalena</strong></p>
<p><span>This morning the tour will take you to visit another of Sardinia’s idyllic nearby islands, Isola Maddalena. From Palau take the ferry across to the town of La Maddalena (approx. 20 minutes). Once you’re here you’ll feel like you have landed on the shores of the Caribbean, with its crystal clear waters and white sandy beaches. The small island has an interesting history. Inhabited since the prehistoric ages, it has changed hands and even its name several times. Expect to relax in this stunning location that takes you away from the well-beaten tourist trails to explore its beautiful beaches and rocky coves. After a day of exploring you’ll head back to your hotel in Porto Cervo.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Aggius and <span>Castelsardo </span></strong></p>
<p><span>Head away from the coast and further inland. Today on the tour you’ll have the chance to see some of the inner regions of Sardinia. The first stop will be in the picturesque village of Aggius that's surrounded by striking granite mountains and gnarled cork oaks that date back hundreds of years. The town is famed for its traditional crafts, here you’ll get to learn about these crafts and techniques with a visit to the local cork museum. Next, head to Castelsardo on the north-west coast of the island. This medieval town towers above the sea and the surrounding landscape. Explore the ancient alleyways as you visit the town’s churches of Santa Mairia delle Grazie and Saint Antonio Abate, as well as the fortress and museum. Later in the afternoon, you'll arrive at you hotel in Alghero.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Alghero and Capo Caccia</strong></p>
<p><span>Alghero is famed for its medieval citadel and cobbled streets. In the morning you’ll have the chance to explore this historic town. Enter through the 14</span><sup>th</sup><span> Century gates to the city and take in the town's fascinating sights including the Catedrale di Santa Maria and the church of Saint Francesco. Alghero is one of the only remaining Italian cities with its walls and bastions still intact. The town is filled with small cafes and bars so you’ll have plenty of spots to choose from for a light or leisurely lunch (payable locally). In the afternoon, you’ll see the impressive limestone cliffs of Capo Caccia. </span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Bosa</strong></p>
<p><span>In the morning, you’ll have free time to relax before heading to the beautiful town of Bosa. Enjoy the drive through the striking Sardinian landscape. As you draw closer to the town, you’ll be stuck by the rainbow-coloured houses stacked in the hillside above the glossy winding Temo River. Spend some time exploring the old village, before heading back to Alghero.</span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Dinner</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: Olbia - UK</strong></p>
<p><span>On the last day you will be taken to Olbia Airport for your flight home. </span></p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/secrets-of-sardinia#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>7 nights accommodation</li>
<li>7 breakfasts and 7 dinners</li>
<li>Walking tour of Porto Cervo</li>
<li>Visit to Capo Testa</li>
<li>Full day excursion to Corsica and Isola Maddalena</li>
<li>Visit Aggius</li>
<li>Walking tour of Alghero</li>
<li>Afternoon excursion to Bosa</li>
<li>Airport transfers</li>
</ul>
<p><span></span><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Entrance tickets to museums/archaeological sites</li>
<li>Hotel city taxes (approx. €6pppn)</li>
<li>Extras, drinks and personal expenses</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/secrets-of-sardinia#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Luci Di La Muntagna, </strong><strong>Porto Cervo (4 nights)</strong></p>
<p>Located in an area of natural beauty, the Luci Di La Muntagna Hotel provides a tranquil retreat in the heart of the Costa Smerelda. The whitewashed Mediterranean style hotel is close to the marina and offers beautiful views over the glistening water in the bay and is just a short stroll from the centre of town.  A large swimming pool with parasols and loungers looks out over the bay, creating a lovely setting to relax. In the evening the hotel's restaurant serves traditional Mediterranean cuisine. The simple rooms are light and fresh with cool tiled floors.</p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Punta Negra, </strong><strong>Alghero (3 nights)</strong></p>
<p>Set in an idyllic location on Sardinia’s west coast, the Hotel Punta Negra, has lovely views across the Mediterranean Sea. The hotel boasts two swimming pools set atop the cliffs overlooking the sea. The hotel has plenty of places to relax and unwind, including its own private beach. The rooms are light and airy, decorated in soft colours with typical Mediterranean characteristics. The hotel provides an American buffet breakfast and the La Luna restaurant serves typical Italian cuisine. </p>
<p><strong>Your Food:<span> </span></strong>In the morning help yourself to the continental breakfast buffet. For your evening meal there is a three course menu, with a choice of 2-3 pastas, 2-3 main courses with side dish plus dessert or fruit. </p>
<p> </p>
